Name: Oregon Shakespeare Festival Association
Certified Representative: International Alliance of Theatrical Stage Employees, Moving Picture Technicians, Artists and Allied Crafts of the United States, its Territories and Canada, Local 154
Unit Sought:
Add-On Voting Group:
All full-time and part-time Physical Plant employees employed by the Employer; but excluding all managers, confidential employees, and guards and supervisors as defined by the Act.
Existing Unit:
The parties' current CBA (2022-2025) contains the following recognition clause:
''The Employer hereby recognizes the Union as the sole and exclusive bargaining representative for: all Production Department Employees in the Stage Operations, Wardrobe, Hair & Wig, Lighting & Video, Sound, Scene Shop and Properties Departments of Oregon Shakespeare Festival. This Agreement excludes all supervisors, managers, and confidential employees as defined by the National Labor Relations Act and all other OSF employees, including but not limited to resident artistic staff, designers, actors, stage managers, costume shop staff, and administrative staff."
After that language was bargained, OSF voluntarily recognized and agreed to add to the exiting unit: "All full time and regular part-time Costume Department employees employed by the Employer," but excluding "All managers, confidential employees, guards and supervisors as defined in the National Labor Relations Act." The parties are currently bargaining over terms and conditions of employment for the Costume Department employees.
Certification/Recognition History:
The original bargaining unit of run crew employees, which includes several classifications in the stage operations, wardrobe, hair & wig, lighting & video, and sound departments, was certified on June 18, 2015 in Case No. 19-RC-150979.
Following an Armor-Globe petition and election, the scenic and properties shop employees (scenic, painting, and properties employees who perform construction, artistic, automation, and painting work on scenery and properties) were added to the existing unit/certified on January 25, 2022 in Case No. 19-RC-286628.
Following the Union's notice of its intent to file another Armor Globe petition to add the Costume Shop employees to the existing unit, OSF agreed to voluntarily recognize those employees pursuant to a voluntary recognition agreement and FMCS-conducted card check. See Case No. VR-1-3155396831.

Name: Southern Glazer''s Wine and Spirits of Upstate New York, LLC
Unit Sought:
There is no pre-existing unit for identification in response to this portion of the petition. The composition of the proposed unit is presently in dispute.
By way of brief background, on or around August 6, 2020, Teamsters Local 317 (the “Union”) filed a petition for representation of “full & part-time Cycle Counter (inventory control)” employees located at the Employer’s Syracuse, New York warehouse.  The Employer understood this unit to be comprised of its three Cycle Counter employees.  The Union first made the Employer aware of its desire to include an Inventory Control Coordinator in the proposed unit after the Employer’s deadline had passed to submit a position statement where the Employer could challenge the composition of the bargaining unit.  An election was subsequently held on September 9, 2020, where the Employer challenged the ballot of the Inventory Control Coordinator.  That challenged ballot was not sufficient to alter the outcome of the election, so the Employer did not have further opportunity to challenge the Inventory Control Coordinator’s inclusion in the proposed unit.  The Employer has consistently disputed the Inventory Control Coordinator’s inclusion in the unit due to insufficient community of interest and because the position was not clearly identified in the representation petition.  The Union continues to identify the Inventory Control Coordinator as a represented member of the bargaining unit. Accordingly, this unit clarification petition is filed to obtain a determination as to the appropriate scope of the bargaining unit.
